{
  "video_id": "xf8zep5BADs",
  "title": "Mark Forsyth: What's a snollygoster? A short lesson in political speak",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Morton Bast Reviewer: Thu-Huong Ha"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15926.0,
      "end_time": 19507.0,
      "text": "One of my favorite words in the whole of the Oxford English Dictionary"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19531.0,
      "end_time": 21374.0,
      "text": "is \"snollygoster,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21398.0,
      "end_time": 23440.0,
      "text": "just because it sounds so good."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23680.0,
      "end_time": 26457.0,
      "text": "And what snollygoster means is \"a dishonest politician.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 27376.0,
      "end_time": 29906.0,
      "text": "Although there was a 19th-century newspaper editor"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29930.0,
      "end_time": 31963.0,
      "text": "who defined it rather better when he said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 31987.0,
      "end_time": 34503.0,
      "text": "\"A snollygoster is a fellow who seeks office"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 34527.0,
      "end_time": 38110.0,
      "text": "regardless of party, platform or principle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 38134.0,
      "end_time": 39642.0,
      "text": "and who, when he wins,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 39666.0,
      "end_time": 44890.0,
      "text": "gets there by the sheer force of monumental talknophical assumnancy.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44914.0,
      "end_time": 46443.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46467.0,
      "end_time": 48565.0,
      "text": "Now, I have no idea what \"talknophical\" is."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 48589.0,
      "end_time": 50391.0,
      "text": "Something to do with words, I assume."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 50415.0,
      "end_time": 53690.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s very important that words are at the center of politics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53714.0,
      "end_time": 56919.0,
      "text": "and all politicians know they have to try and control language."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56943.0,
      "end_time": 59971.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t until, for example, 1771"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 59995.0,
      "end_time": 64417.0,
      "text": "that the British Parliament allowed newspapers to report"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 64441.0,
      "end_time": 67214.0,
      "text": "the exact words that were said in the debating chamber."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 67714.0,
      "end_time": 70110.0,
      "text": "And this was actually all down to the bravery"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 70350.0,
      "end_time": 73344.0,
      "text": "of a guy with the extraordinary name of Brass Crosby,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 73368.0,
      "end_time": 75940.0,
      "text": "who took on Parliament."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 75118.0,
      "end_time": 77196.0,
      "text": "And he was thrown into the Tower of London"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 77220.0,
      "end_time": 79314.0,
      "text": "and imprisoned,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 79338.0,
      "end_time": 82146.0,
      "text": "but he was brave enough,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 82171.0,
      "end_time": 84650.0,
      "text": "he was brave enough to take them on, and in the end,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 84674.0,
      "end_time": 87109.0,
      "text": "he had such popular support in London that he won."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 87133.0,
      "end_time": 88896.0,
      "text": "And it was only a few years later"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 88920.0,
      "end_time": 93791.0,
      "text": "that we have the first recorded use of the phrase \"as bold as brass.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 94321.0,
      "end_time": 96345.0,
      "text": "Most people think that&#39;s down to the metal."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 96369.0,
      "end_time": 100199.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not; it&#39;s down to a campaigner for the freedom of the press."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 100811.0,
      "end_time": 104997.0,
      "text": "But to really show you how words and politics interact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 105210.0,
      "end_time": 107641.0,
      "text": "I want to take you back to the United States of America,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 107665.0,
      "end_time": 110290.0,
      "text": "just after they&#39;d achieved independence."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 110469.0,
      "end_time": 112217.0,
      "text": "And they had to face the question"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 112241.0,
      "end_time": 114946.0,
      "text": "of what to call George Washington, their leader."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 114970.0,
      "end_time": 116226.0,
      "text": "They didn&#39;t know."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 116250.0,
      "end_time": 119206.0,
      "text": "What do you call the leader of a republican country?"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 119595.0,
      "end_time": 122462.0,
      "text": "And this was debated in Congress for ages and ages."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 122486.0,
      "end_time": 125180.0,
      "text": "And there were all sorts of suggestions on the table,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 125420.0,
      "end_time": 126237.0,
      "text": "which might have made it."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 126261.0,
      "end_time": 128497.0,
      "text": "I mean, some people wanted him to be called"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 128520.99999999999,
      "end_time": 130310.99999999999,
      "text": "\"Chief Magistrate Washington,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 130336.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132825.0,
      "text": "and other people, \"His Highness, George Washington,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 132849.0,
      "end_time": 134830.0,
      "text": "and other people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 134107.0,
      "end_time": 136865.0,
      "text": "\"Protector of the Liberties"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 136889.0,
      "end_time": 139940.0,
      "text": "of the People of the United States of America Washington.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 139964.0,
      "end_time": 141300.0,
      "text": "Not that catchy."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 141607.0,
      "end_time": 144410.0,
      "text": "Some people just wanted to call him king --"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 144650.0,
      "end_time": 145571.0,
      "text": "it was tried and tested."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 145595.0,
      "end_time": 147325.0,
      "text": "They weren&#39;t even being monarchical,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 147349.0,
      "end_time": 150563.0,
      "text": "they had the idea that you could be elected king for a fixed term."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 150587.0,
      "end_time": 152851.0,
      "text": "And, you know, it could have worked."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 152875.0,
      "end_time": 154733.0,
      "text": "And everybody got insanely bored,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 154757.0,
      "end_time": 156831.0,
      "text": "because this debate went on for three weeks."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 156855.0,
      "end_time": 159845.0,
      "text": "I read a diary of this poor senator who just keeps coming back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 159869.0,
      "end_time": 161117.0,
      "text": "\"Still on this subject.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 161141.0,
      "end_time": 163670.0,
      "text": "And the reason for the delay and the boredom"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 163694.0,
      "end_time": 167309.0,
      "text": "was that the House of Representatives were against the Senate."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 167333.0,
      "end_time": 171550.0,
      "text": "The House of Representatives didn&#39;t want Washington to get drunk on power."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 171574.0,
      "end_time": 174661.0,
      "text": "They didn&#39;t want to call him \"king,\" in case that gave him ideas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 174685.0,
      "end_time": 176250.0,
      "text": "or his successor ideas."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 176490.0,
      "end_time": 179196.0,
      "text": "So they wanted to give him the humblest, meagerest,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 179220.0,
      "end_time": 181867.0,
      "text": "most pathetic title that they could think of."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 182616.0,
      "end_time": 183846.0,
      "text": "And that title ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 184704.0,
      "end_time": 186990.0,
      "text": "was \"President.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 186123.0,
      "end_time": 188186.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 188211.0,
      "end_time": 190238.0,
      "text": "\"President.\" They didn&#39;t invent the title."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 190262.0,
      "end_time": 191584.0,
      "text": "I mean, it existed before,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 191608.0,
      "end_time": 194273.0,
      "text": "but it just meant somebody who presides over a meeting."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 194297.0,
      "end_time": 196180.0,
      "text": "It was like the foreman of the jury."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 196204.0,
      "end_time": 198400.0,
      "text": "And it didn&#39;t have much more grandeur"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 198640.0,
      "end_time": 199918.0,
      "text": "than the term \"foreman\" or \"overseer.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 199942.0,
      "end_time": 202815.0,
      "text": "There were occasional presidents of little colonial councils"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 202839.0,
      "end_time": 204110.0,
      "text": "and bits of government,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 204350.0,
      "end_time": 205799.0,
      "text": "but it was really a nothing title."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 206250.0,
      "end_time": 208260.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s why the Senate objected to it."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 208284.0,
      "end_time": 212330.0,
      "text": "They said, \"That&#39;s ridiculous! You can&#39;t call him &#39;President.&#39;"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 212570.0,
      "end_time": 215476.0,
      "text": "This guy has to go and sign treaties and meet foreign dignitaries."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 215500.0,
      "end_time": 219550.0,
      "text": "Who&#39;s going to take him seriously if he&#39;s got a silly little title"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 219790.0,
      "end_time": 221720.0,
      "text": "like &#39;President of the United States of America&#39;?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 221744.0,
      "end_time": 222755.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 222779.0,
      "end_time": 225210.0,
      "text": "And after three weeks of debate, in the end,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 226547.0,
      "end_time": 229245.0,
      "text": "the Senate did not cave in."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 230626.0,
      "end_time": 235486.0,
      "text": "Instead, they agreed to use the title \"President\" for now."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 236316.0,
      "end_time": 239100.0,
      "text": "But they also wanted it absolutely set down"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 239124.0,
      "end_time": 240941.0,
      "text": "that they didn&#39;t agree with it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 242229.0,
      "end_time": 247678.0,
      "text": "from a decent respect for the opinions and practice of civilized nations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 247702.0,
      "end_time": 251506.0,
      "text": "whether under republican or monarchical forms of government,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 251530.0,
      "end_time": 253644.0,
      "text": "whose custom it is to annex,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 253668.0,
      "end_time": 255684.0,
      "text": "through the office of the Chief Magistrate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 255708.0,
      "end_time": 257839.0,
      "text": "titles of respectability --"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 258512.0,
      "end_time": 259759.0,
      "text": "not bloody \"President.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 260642.0,
      "end_time": 263364.0,
      "text": "And that, in the intercourse with foreign nations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 264270.0,
      "end_time": 267517.0,
      "text": "the majesty of the people of the United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 267541.0,
      "end_time": 271524.0,
      "text": "may not be hazarded by an appearance of singularity --"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 271548.0,
      "end_time": 273960.0,
      "text": "i.e., we don&#39;t want to look like bloody weirdos."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 275745.0,
      "end_time": 278350.0,
      "text": "Now, you can learn three interesting things from this."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 278374.0,
      "end_time": 280571.0,
      "text": "First of all -- and this is my favorite --"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 280595.0,
      "end_time": 283310.0,
      "text": "is that, so far as I&#39;ve ever been able to find out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 283550.0,
      "end_time": 287359.0,
      "text": "the Senate has never formally endorsed the title of President."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 288351.0,
      "end_time": 291270.0,
      "text": "Barack Obama, President Obama, is there on borrowed time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 291294.0,
      "end_time": 294433.0,
      "text": "just waiting for the Senate to spring into action."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 294458.0,
      "end_time": 295704.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 295728.0,
      "end_time": 297180.0,
      "text": "The second thing you can learn"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 297204.0,
      "end_time": 300424.0,
      "text": "is that, when a government says that this is a temporary measure --"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 300448.0,
      "end_time": 302816.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 302840.0,
      "end_time": 307210.0,
      "text": "you can still be waiting 223 years later."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 308114.0,
      "end_time": 311630.0,
      "text": "But the third thing you can learn -- and this is the really important one,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 311654.0,
      "end_time": 313378.0,
      "text": "the point I want to leave you on --"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 313402.0,
      "end_time": 317334.0,
      "text": "is that the title, \"President of the United States of America,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 317358.0,
      "end_time": 320663.0,
      "text": "doesn&#39;t sound that humble at all these days, does it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 321504.0,
      "end_time": 324703.0,
      "text": "Something to do with the slightly over 5,000"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 324727.0,
      "end_time": 326977.0,
      "text": "nuclear warheads he has at his disposal"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 327100.0,
      "end_time": 329174.0,
      "text": "and the largest economy in the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 329198.0,
      "end_time": 331717.0,
      "text": "and a fleet of drones and all that sort of stuff."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 332797.0,
      "end_time": 338766.0,
      "text": "Reality and history have endowed that title with grandeur."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 339751.0,
      "end_time": 341369.0,
      "text": "And so the Senate won in the end."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 341393.0,
      "end_time": 343820.0,
      "text": "They got their title of respectability."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 343845.0,
      "end_time": 347381.0,
      "text": "And also, the Senate&#39;s other worry, the appearance of singularity --"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 347405.0,
      "end_time": 349529.0,
      "text": "well, it was a singularity back then."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 349553.0,
      "end_time": 352402.0,
      "text": "But now, do you know how many nations have a president?"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 352426.0,
      "end_time": 354209.0,
      "text": "A hundred and forty-seven."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 354772.0,
      "end_time": 356783.0,
      "text": "All because they want to sound like the guy"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 356807.0,
      "end_time": 359359.0,
      "text": "who&#39;s got the 5,000 nuclear warheads, etc."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 361415.0,
      "end_time": 364294.0,
      "text": "And so, in the end, the Senate won"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 364318.0,
      "end_time": 366775.0,
      "text": "and the House of Representatives lost ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 367823.0,
      "end_time": 370339.0,
      "text": "because nobody&#39;s going to feel that humble"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 370363.0,
      "end_time": 372500.0,
      "text": "when they&#39;re told that they are now"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 372740.0,
      "end_time": 375106.0,
      "text": "the President of the United States of America."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 376503.0,
      "end_time": 379269.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s the important lesson I think you can take away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 379293.0,
      "end_time": 381680.0,
      "text": "and the one I want to leave you with."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 381920.0,
      "end_time": 384885.0,
      "text": "Politicians try to pick and use words to shape and control reality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 384910.0,
      "end_time": 386568.0,
      "text": "but in fact,"
